title: 'It's a big, beautiful species': New giant trapdoor spider discovered in Australia
description: A new and "rare" species of giant trapdoor spider has been discovered in Australia.

title: UK accuses Putin of spreading false information over depleted uranium in tank shells for Ukraine
description: The UK has accused Russian President Vladimir Putin of deliberately spreading false information about a British decision to send tank shells that contain depleted uranium to Ukraine.

title: UK defence spending as share of GDP falls despite Russia's war in Ukraine
description: UK defence spending as a share of national income fell last year compared with 2021 despite Russia's war in Ukraine, new figures released by NATO have revealed.

title: Bad Bunny's ex-girlfriend sues Spotify's most-streamed artist for $40m over voice recording
description: Bad Bunny's ex-girlfriend is suing the Puerto Rican musician for at least $40m over a voice recording of hers that he used in two of his songs.

title: Coal miner's confession of killing wife was lawfully obtained, Cyprus court rules
description: A court in Cyprus has ruled the confession of a British man to killing his terminally ill wife was obtained lawfully and can be used in evidence against him.

title: Russia says it scrambled fighter jet to intercept two US bombers over Baltic Sea
description: A Russian Su-35 fighter jet was scrambled to intercept two US strategic bombers over the Baltic Sea, Russia's defence ministry has said.

title: 100m-high wall of sand towers above Chinese region during storm
description: Strong wind, sandstorms and concentrated dust are battering northern China - causing travel chaos and damaging property.

title: COVID data from animal market 'gives clues on origins of virus'
description: Data from the early stages of the COVID-19 pandemic has provided crucial information on the outbreak's origins, according to researchers.

title: Screening of Winnie the Pooh slasher film cancelled in Hong Kong
description: The screening of a new Winnie the Pooh slasher film has been cancelled in Hong Kong due to technical reasons, according to reports.

title: Sri Lanka to receive $3bn bailout - but government faces corruption probe
description: Sri Lanka is to receive $3bn (£2.44bn) as part of a bailout plan to help the bankrupt nation which is also facing a humanitarian crisis.

title: A region of Antarctica has lost 3,000 billion tonnes of ice - enough to cover London with 2km of snow
description: More than 3,000 billion tonnes of ice has been lost in the Antarctic's fastest-changing region - the Amundsen Sea Embayment - in just 25 years.

title: 'She slammed him very hard': Gwyneth Paltrow hit fellow skier directly in back before bolting, court hears
description: Gwyneth Paltrow "slammed very hard" into a fellow skier, hitting him directly in the back, as he fell face down, lying "spread-eagled" in the snow, a US court has heard.

title: Gwyneth Paltrow appears in court accused of causing brain injury to man in ski crash
description: Gwyneth Paltrow has appeared in court in the US over claims she seriously injured a man in a "hit-and-run" skiing crash in 2016.

title: Dentist accused of killing wife by lacing protein shakes with poison
description: Police in Colorado believe a dentist killed his wife by lacing her pre-workout protein shakes with arsenic and cyanide, so he could be with a fellow dentist he was having an affair with.

title: Biden vows US will 'declassify' information about COVID's origins
description: Joe Biden has vowed his administration will "declassify" as much information about the origins of COVID-19 as possible - including any potential links to a Chinese research lab.

title: Martina Navratilova reveals she is 'cancer free' after fearing she 'may not see next Christmas'
description: Martina Navratilova has said she is "cancer free" after she had been diagnosed with throat and breast cancers.
